1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
What is this? What happened here?

2
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:12,760
I don't know.

3
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:15,280
Oh, this does not look good.

4
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:18,560
Did anyone see what happened around my desk area this morning?

5
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:22,400
Dwight, I really think someone's probably just playing a prank on you, so just go right through it.

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,140
A prank, huh?

7
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:27,080
This is official police line tape, okay?

8
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:28,240
It's not a prank.

9
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:29,140
Probably is.

10
00:00:29,140 --> 00:00:33,580
Damn it, people! Someone must have seen something!

11
00:00:33,580 --> 00:00:37,860
Oh, you people are useless. Jesus.

12
00:00:37,860 --> 00:00:40,180
Thunder Mifflin, this is Pam.

13
00:00:40,180 --> 00:00:42,260
Hold, please.

14
00:00:42,260 --> 00:00:43,860
Dwight, it's the sheriff.

15
00:00:43,860 --> 00:00:46,740
He said that it's really important it's regarding your desk.

16
00:00:46,740 --> 00:00:47,660
I'll transfer.

17
00:00:47,660 --> 00:00:49,540
Oh, no, no, don't!

18
00:00:49,540 --> 00:00:53,740
I can't...

19
00:00:53,740 --> 00:00:55,100
Just cut through it, man. It's no big deal.

20
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:58,380
This is why I am a volunteer sheriff's deputy and you are not.

21
00:00:58,420 --> 00:01:01,620
Not what?

22
00:01:01,620 --> 00:01:04,660
Wow, man, he really wants to get in touch with you. Maybe it's a murder.

23
00:01:04,660 --> 00:01:05,900
No, there's no blood.

24
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:10,740
Maybe poison? Possibly. My God!

25
00:01:10,740 --> 00:01:13,180
No, Jim, no!

26
00:01:13,180 --> 00:01:14,140
Sheriff!

27
00:01:14,140 --> 00:01:17,820
This is volunteer sheriff's deputy Dwight Schrute.

28
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:24,820
Press the pound key!

29
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:01,620
Have you found a band yet for your wedding?

30
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:02,100
No.

31
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,700
Because I'm in a band.

32
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:05,540
We really rock.

33
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:10,420
Yeah, I mean, it's inevitable. I definitely overhear some wedding preparation, but I'm fine with it.

34
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:12,900
She hears me arranging my social life

35
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:16,700
and we both have to hear Dwight order deer urine over the internet.

36
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:18,340
So it evens out.

37
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:22,380
Oh, I got the save-the-date. Yeah? Yeah, pretty stationery. Oh, thanks.

38
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:28,260
I didn't get mine yet.

39
00:02:28,260 --> 00:02:31,700
There are a few people I decided not to invite.

40
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:35,700
And that might make things kind of awkward, but

41
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:37,820
it's my wedding.

42
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:41,820
And I don't want anyone there who has called me a hussy.

43
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:44,980
Nothing much is happening today.

44
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:49,780
We are having photo IDs taken. Whoop-de-doo.

45
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:55,020
Can't always be like the apprentice.

46
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,220
I know. I'm a big brother.

47
00:02:56,260 --> 00:02:58,900
Something important happens every day.

48
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:02,940
But real life is not like that.

49
00:03:02,940 --> 00:03:04,860
Okay, here we go. One, two...

50
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:08,140
He sometimes wears glasses. Write that down.

51
00:03:08,140 --> 00:03:13,340
Also, that may not be his real hair.

52
00:03:13,340 --> 00:03:17,220
No, wait.

53
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:24,220
Yeah.

54
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:31,220
On or off?

55
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:32,220
Off.

56
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:33,220
Okay.

57
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:36,220
Oh. What is on your face?

58
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:38,220
Is that a disguise?

59
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:40,220
Excuse me.

60
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:43,220
Clown paint.

61
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:46,220
I'm the one who petitioned the office park to have these ID badges taken.

62
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:50,220
So there were no death threats?

63
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:52,220
Let me see your ID.

64
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:54,220
ID badges are long overdue.

65
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:56,220
Security in this office park is a joke.

66
00:03:56,220 --> 00:04:00,220
Last year I came to work with my spud gun in a duffel bag.

67
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:06,220
I sat at my desk all day with a rifle that shoots potatoes at 60 pounds per square inch.

68
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:09,220
Can you imagine if I was deranged?

69
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:19,220
That's not bad.

70
00:04:19,220 --> 00:04:20,220
Hey, do you do weddings?

71
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:23,220
Would you seriously want your wedding photos to look like that?

72
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:34,220
Not bad.

73
00:04:34,220 --> 00:04:36,220
I gave her a higher clearance than you.

74
00:04:36,220 --> 00:04:37,220
What does level red mean?

75
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:39,220
I'd tell you, but I'd have to kill you.

76
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:42,220
Ha ha ha ha!

77
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:47,220
That's a nice tie.

78
00:04:48,220 --> 00:04:50,220
Thank you.

79
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:52,220
That is... who makes that?

80
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:53,220
I don't know.

81
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:55,220
Do you mind if I wear that for the photo?

82
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:59,220
Let's keep our clothes.

83
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:01,220
It's like child abuse.

84
00:05:01,220 --> 00:05:05,220
I say if Jesus saw that, he'd freak out.

85
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:07,220
He'd freak out, Toby.

86
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:08,220
I mean, in so many levels.

87
00:05:08,220 --> 00:05:10,220
And I'm supposed to work there.

88
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:12,220
What's the dealio?

89
00:05:12,220 --> 00:05:14,220
Just sledding Oscar Venn a little.

90
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,220
We would use the break room.

91
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:17,220
The photographer's back there.

92
00:05:17,220 --> 00:05:18,220
What's the problem?

93
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:19,220
Angela.

94
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:22,220
There's just a little dispute over a poster in their workspace.

95
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:24,220
Since Christmas.

96
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:25,220
So what, you're having a little spat?

97
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:27,220
I forget, are you guys dating?

98
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:28,220
No.

99
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:31,220
Michael, can I talk to you for a second, please?

100
00:05:31,220 --> 00:05:33,220
Here's how I usually handle this.

101
00:05:33,220 --> 00:05:35,220
All I do is listen.

102
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:37,220
These things just have a way of working themselves out.

103
00:05:37,220 --> 00:05:40,220
It's like if you write someone a letter when you're really angry

104
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:42,220
and they say to keep it in your drawer for a couple of days,

105
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:44,220
and then you just never end up sending it.

106
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:46,220
What do you know about conflict resolution?

107
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:48,220
Your answer to everything is to get divorced.

108
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:49,220
So...

109
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:50,220
Okay, okay, well...

110
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:52,220
That was the right decision for me, my man.

111
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:54,220
Well, that's not gonna fly here, because in this office,

112
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:56,220
it is still death through its part.

113
00:05:56,220 --> 00:05:58,220
Assuming that we don't get downsized.

114
00:05:58,220 --> 00:06:00,220
Pam?

115
00:06:00,220 --> 00:06:03,220
Would you get Angela and meet us in the conference room, please?

116
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:06,220
A mediator's tool chest.

117
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:11,220
Okay, well, before we get started,

118
00:06:11,220 --> 00:06:16,220
you should know that there are five different styles of conflict.

119
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:20,220
My Shaolin Temple style defeats your monkey style.

120
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:22,220
Can we go? I have a lot of work to do.

121
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,220
Nope, this is important.

122
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:25,220
Okay, the first style is lose-lose.

123
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:26,220
What's the next one?

124
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:29,220
Just hold on, please.

125
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:34,220
Okay, if we do lose-lose, neither of you gets what you want.

126
00:06:34,220 --> 00:06:37,220
Do you understand?

127
00:06:37,220 --> 00:06:39,220
You...

128
00:06:39,220 --> 00:06:41,220
You would both lose.

129
00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:43,220
Now, I need to ask you,

130
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:47,220
do you want to pursue a lose-lose negotiation?

131
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:51,220
Can we just skip to whatever number five is, win-win or whatever?

132
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:56,220
Win-win is number four, and number five is win-win-win.

133
00:06:56,220 --> 00:07:00,220
The important difference here is, with win-win-win, we all win.

134
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,220
Me, too.

135
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:06,220
I win for having successfully mediated a conflict at work.

136
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:09,220
Okay, so this is the disputed poster.

137
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:14,220
Now, one at a time, I want you to express your feelings

138
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:21,220
using I emotion language and no judging or you statements.

139
00:07:21,220 --> 00:07:25,220
I got this poster for Christmas, and I feel I want to see it every day.

140
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:28,220
It makes me feel like the babies are the true artists,

141
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:30,220
and God has a really cute sense of humor.

142
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:32,220
Come on, seriously, that?

143
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:34,220
I don't like looking at it.

144
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:37,220
It's creepy and in bad taste, and it's just offensive to me.

145
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:40,220
It makes me think of the horrible frigid stage mothers

146
00:07:40,220 --> 00:07:42,220
who forced the babies into it.

147
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:44,220
It's kitsch, it's the opposite of art.

148
00:07:44,220 --> 00:07:46,220
It destroys art, it destroys souls.

149
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:49,220
This is so much more offensive to me than hardcore porn.

150
00:07:49,220 --> 00:07:52,220
Okay, okay, okay, stop, stop, stop.

151
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:54,220
Let's see if we can't just brainstorm

152
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:57,220
and find some creative alternatives that are win-win.

153
00:07:57,220 --> 00:07:58,220
Win.

154
00:07:58,220 --> 00:07:59,220
Yes, thank you, Pam.

155
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:02,220
How about Angela makes the poster into a T-shirt?
